Well, this is an unlucky case! You can consider changing your `serializer` to
```
GLOBALS = {
    'serializer': "__version__ = '{{major}}.{{minor}}.{{patch}}'",
}
```

which should do the job. You can also change it only for the `checker.py` file, as shown here http://punch.readthedocs.io/en/latest/ in the `FILES` section. You can have something like this:

```
GLOBALS = {
    'serializer': '{{ major }}.{{ minor }}.{{ patch }}'
}

FILES = [
    'version.txt',
    {
        'path': 'mypkg/__init__.py',
        'serializer': '{{ major }}.{{ minor }}'
    }
]
```

and the serializer will be overridden for that file.

Let me know if this solves the issue!

