Answering here in case it helps anyone else.
You **can** get pycharm and flask apps to work together to allow source level debugging in the REST service handler.
You can also optionally configure the app to attach to a remote debugger:

```
    @api.expect(parser, model_repository['article_input'], validate=True)
    @api.doc(parser=parser)
    @api.marshal_with(model_repository['document'])
    def post(self):
        try:
            if PYDEVD:
                logger.error('PYDEV enabled, attatching to {}'.format(PYDEVD_PORT))
                pydevd.settrace('localhost', port=PYDEVD_PORT)
```
PYDEVD is a debug toggle flag. PYDEVD_PORT is whatever the pycharm instance is listening on.

The solution ended up being that one needs to `pip install pydevd', and include the PyCharm provided /Applications/PyCharm.app/Contents/debug-eggs/pycharm-debug.egg in the PYTHONPATH on the target VM.

Works beautifully.

