@Tarrasch the fix is here. I'm only putting it in for backward compatibility because It's pretty bug prone to implicitly write unicode into a file. That's probably the main reason why I use python3 (it doesn't let you do that). I would suggest that you implicitly encode your data or that you use `luigi.format.UTF8` on your target.

